{{Politics of Liechtenstein}}
'''General elections''' were held in [[Liechtenstein]] on 6 March 1932, with a second round on 13 March.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1164 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> The result was a victory for the ruling [[Progressive Citizens' Party]], which won 13 of the 15 seats in the [[Landtag of Liechtenstein|Landtag]].<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p1182</ref> This was the last election contested by the [[Christian-Social People's Party (Liechtenstein)|Christian-Social People's Party]] before it merged with the [[Liechtenstein Homeland Service]] to form the [[Patriotic Union (Liechtenstein)|Patriotic Union]].
