The '''Solcitani''' also called the '''Sulcitani''' were an ancient people of [[Sardinia]], noted by [[Ptolemy]] (III, 3).  They dwelt at the extreme south part of the island, immediately south of the [[Neapolitani]] and the [[Valentini (ancient people)|Valentini]].  Their chief city was [[Sulci]], adjacent to the modern [[Sant'Antioco]].

