A '''zuria''' is a hooded [[dress (garment)|dress]] worn by the [[Tigrinyas|Tigrinya]] women in [[Eritrea]] and [[Ethiopia]].<ref name="DIGOB Tigrinya">[http://www.digob.com/Tigrinya-eritrea-ethiopia/Tigrinya-Dictionary-eritrea-ethiopia.php Tigrinya dictionary] at DIGOB.com</ref>
Traditional zurias go to the ankles, with a [[gauze]] hood around the head and shoulders. Today{{when|date=February 2018}} a ''zuria'' comes in different forms and designs with an extra sheen due to the [[Fashion trends|demands of fashion]]. Zurias are worn during holidays, weddings, or parties.

